                  <div align="center"></div><font size="2"><span class="diffRemove">Vergo the Cursed One, is one of the hardest bosses in the game.</span> To summon <span class="diffRemove">him,</span> <span class="diffAdd">Vergo</span> you&#39;ll need a Silver Hammer (you get these by <span class="diffRemove">Killing</span><span class="diffAdd">killing</span> the &quot;Bellboy&quot; <span class="diffRemove">monster</span><span class="diffAdd">mini boss</span> in Porto Bello Desolate <span class="diffRemove">Cliff,</span> <span class="diffAdd">Cliff</span> he also has a designated spawn time). He can only be summoned once every <span class="diffRemove">8-9</span><span class="diffAdd">8</span> <span class="diffRemove">hours,</span><span class="diffAdd">9</span> <span class="diffAdd">hours</span> by dragging the Silver hammer to the tomb marked in the area map.<br />
                  <br /></font> <b><font size="2">Recommended Classes:</font></b> <font size="2"><br /></font>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Musketeers</li>
                    <li>Wizards</li>
                    <li>Scouts</li>
                    <li>Emilias</li>
                    <li>Fighters (With Good Armor)</li>
                  </ul><font size="2"><font color="#FF0000"><b><font size="3">Character Instructions:</font></b></font></font> <font color="#FFA500"><b><font size="3"></font> <font size="3"><br />
                  <font size="2">The tanks:<br /></font></font></b></font>
                  <ul>
                    <li><font size="2">You guys are very important <span class="diffRemove">here,</span> <span class="diffAdd">here</span> Follow the orders of the raid leader. Don&#39;t lure the mini bosses if you are not the lurer. Don&#39;t Attack Vergo unless you&#39;re given the instruction to attack him. Don&#39;t use weapons that have <span class="diffRemove">fear, poison,</span> <span class="diffAdd">fear poison</span> burn or <span class="diffRemove">blind.</span><span class="diffAdd">blind but shock is good.</span> Make sure you have metal armor or elite leather armor to at least survive 1 hit of vergo. If you are a Wiz <span class="diffRemove">tanking,</span> <span class="diffAdd">tanking</span> avoid taking more than 1 <span class="diffRemove">character,</span> <span class="diffAdd">character</span> don&#39;t cast <span class="diffRemove">anything,</span> <span class="diffAdd">anything</span> keep clicking your way through the circle and DON&#39;T STOP; one bad move and your whole raid party will be wiped.<br /></font></li>
                  </ul><font color="#0000FF" size="2"><b>The Members:<br /></b></font>
                  <ul>
                    <li><font color="#8C37AD" size="2">Wizards:</font> <font size="2">Your job is to cast protection field on the tanks and damage <span class="diffRemove">dealers,</span> <span class="diffAdd">dealers</span> or tank if the &quot;Circle&quot; is decided to be used to complete Vergo. When killing the Adds (mini bosses) stay with the group and spam <span class="diffRemove">HoD,</span> <span class="diffAdd">HoD</span> you want to stun the enemies so the rest of the group can kill them. Do not cast any other ESP buff besides protection field.<br /></font></li>
                    <li><font size="2"><font color="#808080">Musks</font>: Stay with the <span class="diffRemove">group,</span> <span class="diffAdd">group</span> and kill the adds until the leader makes the call to kill the Canon mini boss. After <span class="diffRemove">that,</span> <span class="diffAdd">that</span> just attack Vergo with normal attacks; don&#39;t use skills.</font></li>
                    <li><font size="2"><font color="#FFA500">Scouts</font>: Keep reviving the fallen <span class="diffRemove">allies,</span> <span class="diffAdd">allies</span> don&#39;t ress the tank&#39;s chars if he is still tanking with one of his characters. Cast the Attack and Speed <span class="diffRemove">buffs,</span> <span class="diffAdd">buffs</span> don&#39;t cast Fortitudo.</font></li>
                    <li><font size="2"><font color="#0000FF">Emilias</font>: You have to keep casting protection <span class="diffRemove">field,</span> <span class="diffAdd">field</span> and ressing the fallen allies. DO NOT CAST OTHER BUFFS.<br /></font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">Fighters: Pure DPS is what you <span class="diffRemove">want,</span> <span class="diffAdd">want</span> DPS and <span class="diffRemove">Defense,</span> <span class="diffAdd">Defense</span> so Javs and Blunts are good here.<br /></font></li>
                  </ul>
                  <ul></ul><font size="2"><font color="#FFA500"><b><font size="3">Recommendations:<br /></font></b></font></font>
                  <ul>
                    <li><font size="2">The Circle is the best way to do this <span class="diffRemove">raid,</span> <span class="diffAdd">raid</span> but its risky and long. If you want your party to finish the quest <span class="diffRemove">fast,</span> <span class="diffAdd">fast</span> just buy AM <span class="diffRemove">boosts,</span> <span class="diffAdd">boosts</span> and attack Vergo from the start. I recommend the circle if your clan is not well equipped.</font><br /></li>
                  </ul>
                  <ul></ul><br />
                  <b><font color="#0000FF">Instructions:<br /></font></b>
                  <ol>
                    <li><font size="2">Make a group in the square on the left side of the square were the tomb is located (talking about the squares in the area <span class="diffRemove">map,</span> <span class="diffAdd">map</span> the &quot;cords&quot; squares).</font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">Make sure everyone&#39;s <span class="diffRemove">buffed,</span> <span class="diffAdd">buffed</span> and ready to go.</font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">Don&#39;t use Defense mode on the <span class="diffRemove">Scouts,</span> <span class="diffAdd">Scouts</span> if you can play in individual mode and use the scout manually when needed.</font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">The raid <span class="diffRemove">leader,</span> <span class="diffAdd">leader</span> drag the silver hammer to the tomb.<br /></font></li>
                  </ol><font size="2"><b>Once he spawns:<br /></b></font>
                  <ol>
                    <li><font size="2">You&#39;ll see a msg in your <span class="diffRemove">screen,</span> <span class="diffAdd">screen</span> and a dialogue by Vergo. Your whole Raid party should by buffed before the hammer is used; why? because after that <span class="diffRemove">msg,</span> <span class="diffAdd">msg</span> there will be over 25 monsters with ice attribute and above level 90 attacking everyone in the group. Stay <span class="diffRemove">calmed,</span> <span class="diffAdd">calmed</span> Wizards should use HoD to stun those <span class="diffRemove">mobs,</span> <span class="diffAdd">mobs</span> then the rest of the people should attack everything.</font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">The Best geared up <span class="diffRemove">player,</span> <span class="diffAdd">player</span> should go to tank Vergo (not literally tank <span class="diffRemove">him,</span> <span class="diffAdd">him</span> just keep vergo on <span class="diffRemove">him,</span> <span class="diffAdd">him</span> while he runs in circles to keep the group safe until they go to kill vergo)<br /></font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">Once you kill those <span class="diffRemove">monsters,</span> <span class="diffAdd">monsters</span> ress every fallen player. Now its time to kill the &quot;Adds&quot; or Mini bosses.</font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">The Raid leader will select one player to go and get 1 of the mini <span class="diffRemove">bosses,</span> <span class="diffAdd">bosses</span> and drag him all the way to the group.<br /></font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">There the group should kill the mini boss (remember that stun will be needed to kill them fast). The mini bosses run away when they get attacked for a certain <span class="diffRemove">time,</span> <span class="diffAdd">time</span> so this can take awhile.</font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">Once you kill the <span class="diffRemove">&quot;Savi-di</span><span class="diffAdd">&quot;Savi</span> <span class="diffAdd">di</span> gavi of <span class="diffRemove">Main&quot;,</span> <span class="diffAdd">Main&quot;</span> &quot;Skeleton Warrior of main&quot; and the &quot;Steel Anchor of <span class="diffRemove">Main&quot;,</span> <span class="diffAdd">Main&quot;</span> its time to kill the Canon Captain of Main.</font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">Musks and wizards should do fine <span class="diffRemove">here,</span> <span class="diffAdd">here</span> just send them to attack the captain and keep ressing the fallen. DO NOT Attack VERGO.</font></li>
                    <li><font size="2"><span class="diffRemove">OK,</span> <span class="diffAdd">OK</span> so you finally finished with the <span class="diffRemove">adds,</span> <span class="diffAdd">adds</span> vergo will be a piece of cake now. Decide what strategy you want to use: A) The Circle | B) Full Attack | C)Whatever</font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">This guide will use the Circle. Select one of the Wizards from the team (the one that rarely <span class="diffRemove">lags,</span> <span class="diffAdd">lags</span> or that has less lag than anyone else). Send him to take the Aggro of vergo <span class="diffRemove">(yes,</span> <span class="diffAdd">(yes</span> that <span class="diffRemove">means,</span> <span class="diffAdd">means</span> attacking vergo <span class="diffRemove">once,</span> <span class="diffAdd">once</span> after vergo kills the first tank).</font></li>
                    <li><font size="2"><span class="diffRemove">Now,</span> <span class="diffAdd">Now</span> the group should form a circle in the map (the smaller the better) of people. The best way to do this is building a <span class="diffRemove">turret,</span> <span class="diffAdd">turret</span> and everyone moves to the center of the turret.</font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">The Wiz Tank will have to drag vergo and keep going in &quot;circles&quot; around the players. Vergo wont attack them because he has aggro on the <span class="diffRemove">wizard,</span> <span class="diffAdd">wizard</span> so the team should be fine as long as the wizard is alive.<br /></font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">Wizard &lt; Keep going in circles around the <span class="diffRemove">group,</span> <span class="diffAdd">group</span> and don&#39;t you dare to stop.<br /></font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">Group &lt; don&#39;t use high graphics <span class="diffRemove">buffs,</span> <span class="diffAdd">buffs</span> remember that a little lag can bring the wiz tank down with 1 blow of vergo.<br /></font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">This is how the &quot;circle&quot; should go &gt; <img align="bottom" alt="The Circle" height="233" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/1/GK1xQUNXUXMDKb00R91Z_g10450/GW307H233" title="The Circle" width="307" /> Vergo&#39;s the Red <span class="diffRemove">line,</span> <span class="diffAdd">line</span> the wizard should keep going in circles around the <span class="diffRemove">group,</span> <span class="diffAdd">group</span> while the group attacks vergo.<br /></font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">Everyone in the group should be attacking vergo now. The life should be going down quite moderately.</font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">Once Vergo <span class="diffRemove">dies,</span> <span class="diffAdd">dies</span> he will drop a Key that should be used in the <a href="/page/Treasure+Chest+of+the+Quay" target="_self">Treasure Chest</a> that&#39;s on a ship wreck in Porto Bello quay.</font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">There you go =P now you have your reward</font><br /></li>
                  </ol>
